    Z "Sólo he venido a por el coche."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1275
translate spanish d6b18_c9cf0335_1:

    # Z "If I can make it before sundown, I won't need your hospitality."
    Z "Si consigo llegar antes del atardecer, no necesitaré tu hospitalidad."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1276
translate spanish d6b18_3e3ad588_1:

    # Z "But we will see how it goes..."
    Z "Pero ya veremos cómo va..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1279
translate spanish d6b18_de375b8e_1:

    # Asa "Hmm.. what a shame..."
    Asa "Umm... qué pena..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1282
translate spanish d6b18_a4cb4864:

    # Asa "You should go get the car then."
    Asa "Deberías ir a por el coche entonces."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1283
translate spanish d6b18_92ef027a_1:

    # Z "Thank you, I will."
    Z "Gracias, lo haré."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1290
translate spanish d6b31_7906ea43:

    # "{i}Some time later..."
    "{i}Pasado un tiempo...{/i}"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1297
translate spanish d6b31_ca792ce4:

    # Zt "This should be the place."
    Zt "Este debería ser el lugar."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1298
translate spanish d6b31_696c0fec:

    # "You approach the large, desolated area. Metal shacks, scrap and spare parts fill the place."
    "Te acercas a la gran zona desolada. Chabolas metálicas, chatarra y piezas de repuesto llenan el lugar."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1301
translate spanish d6b31_bcf7700a:

    # "Whoever lived or took shelter here must have built a small community. The presence of palm trees suggests this place once stood atop an oasis, seemingly long gone."
    "Quienquiera que viviera o se refugiara aquí debió haber formado una pequeña comunidad. La presencia de palmeras sugiere que este lugar se alzaba sobre un oasis, aparentemente ya desaparecido."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1302
translate spanish d6b31_6e72d6c8:

    # "What became of them -whether the scavengers fled or perished- remains a mystery."
    "Qué fue de ellos —si los carroñeros huyeron o murieron— sigue siendo un misterio."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1303
translate spanish d6b31_e2e8dfc4:

    # "But not an unusual one. Out here, deep in the desert, lives vanish as swiftly as the wind sweeps away the sand."
    "Pero no es raro. Aquí, en lo profundo del desierto, las vidas desaparecen tan rápido como el viento arrastra la arena."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1307
translate spanish d6b31_d9faf903:

    # Zt "The car I'm looking for should be in one of those containers."
    Zt "El coche que estoy buscando debería estar en uno de esos contenedores."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1314
translate spanish d6b31_d45e335d:

    # Zt "Let's see... two..."
    Zt "Veamos... dos..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1317
translate spanish d6b31_6013d301:

    # Zt "Three..."
    Zt "Tres..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1320
translate spanish d6b31_e070ae5a:

    # Zt "And one already open."
    Zt "Y ya hay una abierta."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1323
translate spanish d6b31_bb2abb9c:

    # Zt "Let's check this one first..."
    Zt "Revisemos este primero..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1325
translate spanish d6b31_b412790e:

    # Zt "It would be nice if Igor's lead brought us something valuable..."
    Zt "Sería agradable si la pista de Igor nos trajera algo valioso..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1332
translate spanish d6b31_737661ab:

    # Zt "The sands of time and... well... the sand, seem to have done some fatal damage to this car. A pity."
    Zt "Las arenas del tiempo y... bueno... la arena, parecen haber causado un daño fatal a este coche. Una lástima."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1335
translate spanish d6b31_1b9561dc:

    # Zt "How about that container..."
    Zt "¿Qué tal ese contenedor?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1338
translate spanish d6b31_2beff89f:

    # Zt "These doors are heavy..."
    Zt "Estas puertas son pesadas..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1342
translate spanish d6b31_f6c35e2d:

    # Zt "..."
    Zt "..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1346
translate spanish d6b31_f6c35e2d_1:

    # Zt "..."
    Zt "..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1347
translate spanish d6b31_640e4b84:

    # Zt "I must be dreaming..."
    Zt "Debo estar soñando..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1351
translate spanish d6b31_54b0e6f9:

    # "{i}You open the container doors..."
    "{i}Abres las puertas del container..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1354
translate spanish d6b31_a46ef0ff:

    # Z "I have to be the luckiest fucking man in the world."
    Z "Tengo que ser el puto hombre más afortunado del mundo."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1355
translate spanish d6b31_d54fa884:

    # Zt "How do we get you out of there..."
    Zt "¿Cómo te sacamos de ahí...?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1359
translate spanish d6b31_58347afa:

    # "{i}You connect the cars with a chain and slowly pull the pickup out of the half sunken container."
    "{i}Unes los coches con una cadena y sacas lentamente la camioneta del container medio hundido."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1360
translate spanish d6b31_16977618:

    # "{i}You don't remember ever hearing of a car that wasn't a ragtag collection of parts of at least half a dozen other cars, let alone seeing one."
    "{i}No recuerdas haber oído hablar de un coche que no fuera una colección de piezas de al menos media docena de otros coches, y mucho menos haber visto uno."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1363
translate spanish d6b31_c9a8869e:

    # "{i}It must've been sealed tight for all this time."
    "{i}Debe haber estado sellado todo este tiempo."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1364
translate spanish d6b31_bdb0b8c9:

    # "{i}Sure, there's a lot of rust, but it still looks great."
    "{i}Claro que hay mucho óxido, pero sigue teniendo un aspecto estupendo."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1367
translate spanish d6b31_5d9b6d1a:

    # "{i}You came prepared with tools and years of experience building and then patching up your old ride."
    "{i}Has venido preparado con herramientas y años de experiencia en la construcción y posterior reparación de tu viejo vehículo."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1368
translate spanish d6b31_3f87c416:

    # "{i}You toss away the old battery and use the one from your car."
    "{i}Tiras la batería vieja y utilizas la de tu coche."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1372
translate spanish d6b31_02ca89e1:

    # Z "I would've dragged you back home, but..."
    Z "Te habría arrastrado de vuelta a casa, pero..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1373
translate spanish d6b31_52136239:

    # Z "Maybe it's better you get your final rest out here."
    Z "Tal vez sea mejor que tengas tu último descanso aquí."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1374
translate spanish d6b31_42468892:

    # Z "We have gone through so much, you and me."
    Z "Hemos pasado por mucho, tú y yo."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1375
translate spanish d6b31_5b63aac1:

    # Z "Rest in peace, old friend..."
    Z "Descansa en paz, viejo amigo..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1378
translate spanish d6b31_5ab3574d:

    # Z "..."
    Z "..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1382
translate spanish d6b31_264b9568:

    # Z "You have sat in the dark, waiting to get on the road for long enough..."
    Z "Te has sentado en la oscuridad, esperando a salir a la carretera durante mucho tiempo..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1383
translate spanish d6b31_77a4f4ba:

    # Z "Let's see how you fare in the dunes, shall we...?"
    Z "Veamos cómo te va en las dunas."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1390
translate spanish d6b31_2bf19ea4:

    # "{i}With a soft rumble that sounds like a magical melody to your ears, the engine starts..."
    "{i}Con un suave rugido que suena como una melodía mágica en tus oídos, el motor arranca..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1395
translate spanish d6b31_1dae6843:

    # Zt "I wonder how long these windows will last..."
    Zt "Me pregunto cuánto durarán estas ventanas..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1405
translate spanish d6b53_161cdb8b:

    # "{i}You eventually get back to Asani's shack..."
    "{i}Finalmente llegas a la choza de Asani..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1409
translate spanish d6b53_6b63c11b:

    # Z "I'm back, and yes, I found it."
    Z "He vuelto, y sí, lo he encontrado."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1412
translate spanish d6b53_6ab385f7:

    # Z "Hello?"
    Z "¿Hola?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1415
translate spanish d6b53_ba01dbdb:

    # Zt "Where is she?"
    Zt "¿Dónde está?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1419
translate spanish d6b53_d6e3e793:

    # Z "These are Zetan coins..."
    Z "Estas son monedas zetanas..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1422
translate spanish re_d6b53_24b8d12f:

    # Asa "Well look at you..."
    Asa "Pues mírate..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1423
translate spanish re_d6b53_a6271b43:

    # Asa "I'm gone for just a few minutes and that's when you decide to show up?"
    Asa "¿Me voy por unos minutos y es cuando decides aparecer?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1426
translate spanish re_d6b53_6557497b:

    # Z "Oh my..."
    Z "Oh vaya..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1429
translate spanish re_d6b53_6a59645d:

    # Asa "I see that you've found a working car... and your way back to me."
    Asa "Veo que has encontrado un coche que funciona... y tu camino de vuelta a mí."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1432
translate spanish re_d6b53_ed228e98:

    # Asa "Are you here to claim your second prize of the day?"
    Asa "¿Estás aquí para reclamar tu segundo premio del día?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1441
translate spanish re_d6b53_f1a99089:

    # Asaw "{i}I'm all yours, as promised..."
    Asaw "{i}Soy toda tuya, como te prometí..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1444
translate spanish re_d6b53_07242ee7:

    # "{i}..."
    "{i}..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1447
translate spanish re_d6b53_9249f00a:

    # Asaw "Hmm..."
    Asaw "Hmm..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1450
translate spanish re_d6b53_9a28d5cb:

    # Asaw "Are you trying to decide if you like my tits or my ass more?"
    Asaw "¿Estás intentando decidir si te gustan más mis tetas o mi culo?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1453
translate spanish re_d6b53_dab65a90:

    # Asaw "Mmmh...such a firm grip..."
    Asaw "Mmmh... un agarre muy firme..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1456
translate spanish re_d6b53_579f313a:

