    Z "Ya lo veremos cuando vuelva a ocurrir."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1714
translate spanish d6b103_ceacd633:

    # Asa "You've actually been there and made it out alive?"
    Asa "¿Realmente has estado allí y has salido con vida?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1715
translate spanish d6b103_7762c3b7:

    # Z "How else did you think I got the directions to find you?"
    Z "¿De qué otra forma crees que obtuve las indicaciones para encontrarte?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1716
translate spanish d6b103_dfe9b4ed:

    # Asa "You're going to have to tell me what the story is between you and Kyra!"
    Asa "Vas a tener que contarme cuál es la historia entre tú y Kyra."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1717
translate spanish d6b103_f36564f7:

    # Z "Come back to bed, and I will..."
    Z "Vuelve a la cama, y lo haré..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1719
translate spanish d6b103_3b9ea6da:

    # Z "Stranger things have happened, I'm sure..."
    Z "Cosas más extrañas han sucedido, estoy seguro..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1720
translate spanish d6b103_446f5289:

    # Asa "They'd probably steal every part of it, or fight each others to claim it."
    Asa "Probablemente robarían cada parte, o lucharían entre ellas para reclamarla."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1721
translate spanish d6b103_4bf250b1:

    # Z "Let's hope for the latter.... Now come back inside. Let's go back to bed."
    Z "Esperemos que sea así.... Ahora vuelve a entrar. Volvamos a la cama."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1722
translate spanish d6b103_ac8f3ad7:

    # Asa "Yes daddy!"
    Asa "Sí, papí."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1723
translate spanish d6b103_a0182c36:

    # Z "Smart-ass."
    Z "Culito inteligente."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1728
translate spanish d6b103_60c6f4ca:

    # Z "This was a long day, and it ended nicely, but I do need to sleep now."
    Z "Ha sido un día largo y ha terminado bien, pero necesito dormir ya."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1731
translate spanish d6b103_2c1fe24c:

    # Asa "I would have liked to talk a bit more, but sure. Rest, if you want. You did give me a great time, after all."
    Asa "Me habría gustado hablar un poco más, pero claro. Descansa si quieres. Me lo hiciste pasar muy bien, después de todo."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1732
translate spanish d6b103_94240d83:

    # Asa "I still have a few things to do."
    Asa "Todavía tengo algunas cosas que hacer."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1735
translate spanish d6b103_f9e5ffaa:

    # Z "I will leave you to it. I am sorry for not helping, but I really am shutting down."
    Z "Te dejo con ello. Perdona por no ayudarte, pero de verdad que me estoy apagando."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1738
translate spanish d6b103_8b893db7:

    # Asa "Well then... make yourself comfortable. I will join you in a bit."
    Asa "Bueno, entonces... ponte cómodo. Me reuniré contigo en un rato."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1744
translate spanish d6b103_ac8e3d45:

    # "{i}The following morning..."
    "{i}A la mañana siguiente..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1747
translate spanish d6b103_ee6f0063:

    # Asa "Last night was interesting."
    Asa "Anoche fue interesante."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1750
translate spanish d6b103_d110787c:

    # Z "It was indeed. We should do it again."
    Z "Lo fue, en efecto. Deberíamos volver a hacerlo."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1753
translate spanish d6b103_3a0118b4:

    # Asa "Do you plan on coming in this direction again soon?"
    Asa "¿Piensas volver a venir por aquí pronto?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1756
translate spanish d6b103_22c9b4c5:

    # Z "Hard to say, Stalkers go where there's profit, adventure or a mission to accomplish."
    Z "Difícil de decir, los Acechadores van donde hay beneficio, aventura o una misión que cumplir."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1759
translate spanish d6b103_60f125c2:

    # Asa "Well, see that you find a reason."
    Asa "Bueno, a ver si encuentras una razón."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1760
translate spanish d6b103_16c551a5:

    # Asa "Even in a remote place as this, I get visitors, traders, bedouins... but I could use a friend instead."
    Asa "Incluso en un lugar tan remoto como éste, recibo visitas, comerciantes, beduinos... pero me vendría bien un amigo."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1763
translate spanish d6b103_e6ff3fcd:

    # Asa "...And I hear things, occasionally."
    Asa "... Y oigo cosas, de vez en cuando."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1766
translate spanish d6b103_fc224c34:

    # Z "You hear things?"
    Z "¿Oyes cosas?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1769
translate spanish d6b103_d7bff931:

    # Asa "Raiders and others, still swing by now and then. The occasional juicy bit of news could be interesting for types like you... Stalkers, but also Zetans."
    Asa "Los asaltantes y otros, siguen pasando de vez en cuando. Las jugosas noticias ocasionales pueden ser interesantes para tipos como tú... Acechadores, pero también Zetanos."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1772
translate spanish d6b103_13eaada6:

    # Z "Anything in particular on your mind?"
    Z "¿Tienes algo en particular en mente?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1775
translate spanish d6b103_32c498f3:

    # Asa "Only that you should be careful."
    Asa "Sólo que debes tener cuidado."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1776
translate spanish d6b103_d7429d7a:

    # Asa "Raiders are all stockpiling resources and trying to be more organised in their efforts to control the region."
    Asa "Los asaltantes están acumulando recursos y tratando de ser más organizados en sus esfuerzos por controlar la región."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1777
translate spanish d6b103_87175dc4:

    # Asa "They tell me it's in response to the fact that the Decayed from Old Cairo are also expanding their influence."
    Asa "Me dicen que es en respuesta al hecho de que los Decaídos del Viejo Cairo también están expandiendo su influencia."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1778
translate spanish d6b103_20892c4e:

    # Asa "Apparently they too are getting more organised by the day."
    Asa "Al parecer, ellos también se están organizando cada día más."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1779
translate spanish d6b103_ca5f05d2:

    # Asa "This could all come to a head, and if it becomes an all out war, Zeta will have to pick sides or be swept up, either during the war or by the victor."
    Asa "Todo esto podría llegar a un punto crítico, y si se convierte en una guerra total, Zeta tendrá que elegir un bando o ser arrastrado, ya sea durante la guerra o por el vencedor."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1782
translate spanish d6b103_62daab38:

    # Zt "My own recent experiences with the various factions support some of this. Asani is actually well informed, for a straggler."
    Zt "Mis experiencias recientes con las diversas facciones respaldan algo de esto. Asani está bastante bien informada para ser una rezagada."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1783
translate spanish d6b103_41d83173:

    # Z "I've heard similar stories. Will you be safe, out here?"
    Z "He oído historias similares. ¿Estarás a salvo, aquí fuera?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1786
translate spanish d6b103_f6b88c86:

    # Asa "I told you, I still have people who look after me. I'm a good listener, I guess."
    Asa "Ya te he dicho que todavía tengo gente que me cuida. Supongo que sé escuchar."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1787
translate spanish d6b103_13f83590:

    # Asa "I have my ways."
    Asa "Tengo mis costumbres."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1790
translate spanish d6b103_1f93b904:

    # Z "Even so, be safe, Asani... Friends are hard to come by, and who knows.. maybe that's something we could both learn to be, in time..."
    Z "Aun así, cuídate, Asani... Los amigos son difíciles de encontrar, y quién sabe... quizás eso es algo que ambos podríamos aprender a ser, con el tiempo..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1793
translate spanish d6b103_372ca646:

    # Asa "I have no intention of dying, [persistent.player_name]."
    Asa "No tengo intención de morir, [persistent.player_name]."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1796
translate spanish d6b103_ec770346:

    # Z "Who knows, I might have some business with you in the future."
    Z "Quién sabe, quizá tenga algún negocio contigo en un futuro."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1799
translate spanish d6b103_f60cb8cf:

    # Asa "Well, don't be a stranger then... Friend."
    Asa "Bueno, no seas un extraño entonces... Amigo."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1800
translate spanish d6b103_7480da58:

    # Asa "Now go, your family will be worried sick."
    Asa "Ahora vete, tu familia estará muy preocupada."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1803
translate spanish d6b103_e93cefec:

    # Zt "She's not wrong."
    Zt "No está equivocada."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1809
translate spanish d6b103_0cd8be33:

    # Zt "Time to go home. This is a great find, and I can't wait to show it to [S]."
    Zt "Hora de ir a casa. Este es un gran hallazgo, y estoy deseando enseñárselo a [S]."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1811
translate spanish d6b103_682cd2a6:

    # Zt "I really do owe Igor a big gift."
    Zt "Realmente le debo a Igor un gran regalo."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1813
translate spanish d6b103_0109eb5f:

    # Zt "I guess I can always go see her some other time, now that I know where she lives."
    Zt "Supongo que siempre puedo ir a verla en otro momento, ahora que sé dónde vive."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1819
translate spanish d6b52_17624aa6:

    # "{i}You head back on your way home..."
    "{i}Te diriges de nuevo a tu casa..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1822
translate spanish d6b52_8e06eb7c:

    # "{i}Eventually, you arrive..."
    "{i}Por fin, llegas..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1825
translate spanish d6b52_247e93f3:

    # W "That's not the sound of your [persistent.dad]'s car. Let me go check first."
    W "Ese no es el sonido del coche de tu [persistent.dad]. Déjame ir a comprobarlo primero."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1826
translate spanish d6b52_0226c95b:

    # A "Be careful [persistent.mom]."
    A "Ten cuidado [persistent.mom]."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1827
translate spanish d6b52_e4318135:

    # W "[persistent.player_name!c], is that you?"
    W "[persistent.player_name!c], ¿eres tú?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1831
translate spanish d6b52_4bdce96b:

    # Z "Yes, [W], it's me. You can come out."
    Z "Sí, [W], soy yo. Podéis salir."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1832
translate spanish d6b52_9ddca72d:

    # Z "In fact, come see what I have found in the desert!"
    Z "De hecho, ¡venid a ver lo que he encontrado en el desierto!"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1834
translate spanish d6b52_89b3fac9:

    # Z "This time, Igor has truly outdone himself."
    Z "Esta vez, Igor se ha superado de verdad."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1836
translate spanish d6b52_0811bc2f:

    # Z "The Raiders have come through on their end of the deal."
    Z "Los Asaltantes han cumplido su parte del trato."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1840
translate spanish d6b52_3ef9d557:

    # W "So this is what you found following Igor's lead?"
    W "¿Así que esto es lo que has encontrado siguiendo la pista de Igor?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1842
translate spanish d6b52_83b07b68:

    # W "So that Kyra girl spoke the truth... is this the car she bartered for her freedom?"
    W "Así que esa chica Kyra dijo la verdad... ¿es este el coche que intercambió por su libertad?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1845
translate spanish d6b52_df30d54b:

    # Z "Yes it is. An actual vehicle dating back to the times before the End of Days."
    Z "Sí, lo es. Un vehículo real que se remonta a los tiempos anteriores al Fin de los Días."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1846
translate spanish d6b52_fcc02d80:

    # Z "It took me a while to get it running again, but as you can see, it works. "
    Z "Me costó un poco ponerlo en marcha de nuevo, pero como puedes ver, funciona."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1849
translate spanish d6b52_779f8b2a:

    # A "Can I see it too?"
    A "¿Puedo verlo yo también?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1850
translate spanish d6b52_a84e5760:

    # Z "Of course [A], come closer."
    Z "Por supuesto [A], acércate."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1853
translate spanish d6b52_2a1614c3:

    # A "Wow! What a beast! It's so big!"
    A "¡Guau! ¡Qué bestia! ¡Es muy grande!"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1854
translate spanish d6b52_a1f1133f:

    # Z "Yes, that's what s-"
    Z "Sí, eso es lo que dic..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1855
translate spanish d6b52_c2c9cc07:

    # W "..."
    W "..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1856
translate spanish d6b52_438afb5d:

    # Z "Never mind."
    Z "No importa."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1859
translate spanish d6b52_46e899ca:

    # "{i}As she was out all this time, you and [S] eventually meet in the evening."
    "{i}Como ella estuvo fuera todo este tiempo, tú y [S] acabasteis encontrándoos por la noche."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1860
translate spanish d6b52_b78d86c7:

    # "{i}You tell her everything that happened..."
    "{i}... y le cuentas todo lo que pasó..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1867
translate spanish d6b150_eef4cd55:

    # S "So... do you think what she said is true?"
    S "Entonces... ¿crees que lo que te ha dicho ella es cierto?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1868
translate spanish d6b150_9098fa70:

    # S "I mean... do you think the city could stand up for itself?"
    S "Quiero decir... ¿crees que la ciudad podría defenderse por sí misma?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1870
translate spanish d6b150_cd417cae:

    # S "About that girl Kyra... since she's a raider..."
    S "Sobre esa chica Kyra... ya que es una asaltante..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1871
translate spanish d6b150_20118a59:

    # S "How strong are they anyway?"
    S "¿Cómo son de fuertes?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1872
translate spanish d6b150_ad665a50:

    # S "I've heard some concerns from people in the city that if they would attack, we would be in trouble."
    S "He oído que la gente de la ciudad se preocupa de que si atacan, tendremos problemas."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1873
translate spanish d6b150_c9134901:

    # S "You think they have a point?"
    S "¿Crees que tienen razón?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1875
translate spanish d6b150_5b580976:

    # S "When I was in the city today, someone heard that we were in Old Cairo."
    S "Hoy, cuando estaba en la ciudad, alguien se enteró de que estábamos en el Viejo Cairo."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1876
translate spanish d6b150_31fa47d8:

    # S "He asked me whether or not the decayed were strong, and what would happen if they attack."
    S "Me preguntó si los decaídos eran fuertes o no, y qué pasaría si atacaran."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1877
translate spanish d6b150_0ace4cf6:

    # S "I wonder... do you think Zeta is really safe at this point?"
    S "Me pregunto... ¿crees que Zeta está realmente a salvo en este momento?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1878
translate spanish d6b150_f4bdb7aa:

    # S "Just curious..."
    S "Sólo por curiosidad..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1884
translate spanish d6b150_3062ff81:

    # Z "The Queen's army is strong enough."
    Z "El ejército de la Reina es lo suficientemente fuerte."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1885
translate spanish d6b150_cb0c8553:

    # Z "What I've seen in Old Cairo... they are organized."
    Z "Lo que he visto en el Viejo Cairo... es que ellos están organizados."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1886
translate spanish d6b150_d8ce1b40:

    # Z "And I am not sure how much the Raiders are expanding yet."
    Z "Y no estoy seguro de cuánto se están expandiendo los Asaltantes todavía."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1887
translate spanish d6b150_a2267ed4:

    # Z "But Zeta has existed for 400 years. Even if Asani was right, this won't be the first insurrection or even open war it faces."
    Z "Pero Zeta existe desde hace 400 años. Incluso si Asani tuviera razón, ésta no será la primera insurrección o incluso guerra abierta a la que se enfrente."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1888
translate spanish d6b150_c14d979c:

    # Z "The city endures, always."
    Z "La ciudad perdura, siempre."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1891
translate spanish d6b150_19afa8b3:

    # S "Let us hope for the best."
    S "Esperemos lo mejor."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1893
translate spanish d6b150_6ebcdd5d:

    # S "I don't want this place to become unsafe."
    S "No quiero que este lugar se vuelva inseguro."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1894
translate spanish d6b150_cf3839c5:

    # S "So a strong Zeta is probably our best chance of survival."
    S "Así que un Zeta fuerte es probablemente nuestra mejor oportunidad de supervivencia."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1897
translate spanish d6b150_f9f57b20:

    # Z "I have been around a lot, and the Sacred City gives people hope and courage. It has resources most other factions lack completely."
    Z "He recorrido mucho, y la Ciudad Sagrada da a la gente esperanza y valor. Tiene recursos de los que la mayoría de las otras facciones carecen por completo."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1898
translate spanish d6b150_f04352ee:

    # Z "Should it come to it, we may even have to abandon our house and find refuge within the city itself. But that is a worst case scenario."
    Z "Si se diera el caso, puede que incluso tengamos que abandonar nuestra casa y refugiarnos en la propia ciudad. Pero ese sería en el peor de los casos."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1899
translate spanish d6b150_fbf2e380:

    # Z "Should that woman even be right. She's lied on several other things, and her view on this matter may be tainted by her own experience."
    Z "En caso de que esa mujer tenga razón. Ha mentido en otras cosas, y su opinión sobre este asunto puede estar contaminada por su propia experiencia."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1901
translate spanish d6b150_03e3d09e:

    # S "If the worst should happen, we should consider moving away."
    S "Si ocurriera lo peor, deberíamos considerar la posibilidad de alejarnos."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1902
translate spanish d6b150_fd13ea71:

    # S "There are other places where we can build up again."
    S "Hay otros lugares donde podemos volver a construir."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1905
translate spanish d6b150_76e96c37:

    # Z "I doubt it would be so easy..."
    Z "Dudo que sea tan fácil..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1911
translate spanish d6b150_055560f5:

    # Z "From what I have seen in Old Cairo, they are expanding quite fast."
    Z "Por lo que he visto en el Viejo Cairo, ellos se están expandiendo con bastante rapidez."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1912
translate spanish d6b150_bd8ae9e5:

    # Z "I'm not sure about other factions, but I don't think Zeta can hold up on its own, not this time."
    Z "No estoy seguro de otras facciones, pero no creo que Zeta pueda mantenerse por sí sola, no esta vez."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1913
translate spanish d6b150_823446aa:

    # Z "We have an army, but no technology."
    Z "Tenemos un ejército, pero no tecnología."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1914
translate spanish d6b150_3115266c:

    # Z "I think the Queen should look for allies."
    Z "Creo que la Reina debería buscar aliados."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1918
translate spanish d6b150_bc77b3b2:

    # S "But with whom?"
    S "Pero, ¿con quién?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1920
translate spanish d6b150_102422aa:

    # S "Maybe the mutants you told me about?"
    S "¿Tal vez los mutantes de los que me hablaste?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1921
translate spanish d6b150_bd51bb67:

    # S "I don't know what Zeta has against mutants anyway."
    S "Además, no sé qué tiene Zeta contra los mutantes."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1922
translate spanish d6b150_dcdfc24a:

    # S "They're just people, like us."
    S "Sólo son personas, como nosotros."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1923
translate spanish d6b150_f1e658ef:

    # S "If the Queen would tolerate them inside the city, I'm sure they could find common causes."
    S "Si la reina los tolerara dentro de la ciudad, estoy seguro de que podrían encontrar causas comunes."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1924
translate spanish d6b150_c44004a7:

    # S "Imagine what a force Zeta would be with them on our side!"
    S "¡Imagina la fuerza que tendrían los Zeta con ellos de nuestro lado!"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1927
translate spanish d6b150_16091ff8:

    # Z "Maybe... But the culture of rejecting technology goes back for centuries, and prejudice against mutants is strong."
    Z "Tal vez... Pero la cultura de rechazo a la tecnología se remonta a siglos atrás, y los prejuicios contra los mutantes son fuertes."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1931
translate spanish d6b150_74c7fc08:

    # Z "If I only knew..."
    Z "Si lo supiera..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1934
translate spanish d6b150_18d2be28:

    # S "Maybe there is a way to make peace with the decayed?"
    S "¿Quizás haya una forma de hacer las paces con los decaídos?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1935
translate spanish d6b150_e32b3ca7:

    # S "I mean... sure, they are cannibals..."
    S "Quiero decir... claro, son caníbales..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1936
translate spanish d6b150_089cd5f8:

    # S "But as long as Zeta doesn't sacrifice their own, right?"
    S "Pero mientras Zeta no sacrifique a los suyos, ¿no?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1937
translate spanish d6b150_22daf7ef:

    # S "The same goes for the raiders."
    S "Lo mismo ocurre con los asaltantes."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1938
translate spanish d6b150_2c1bb445:

    # S "Maybe the Queen should look to combine forces with them..."
    S "Tal vez la Reina deba buscar combinar fuerzas con ellos..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1939
translate spanish d6b150_e2799937:

    # S "Zeta would be unstoppable!"
    S "¡Zeta sería imparable!"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1942
translate spanish d6b150_4db8bc45:

    # Z "I'm not sure if Zetans would tolerate decayed or raiders in their city..."
    Z "No estoy seguro de si los Zetas tolerarían a los decaídos o a los asaltantes en su ciudad..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1947
translate spanish d6b150_7de07191:

    # Z "Zeta has been around for centuries."
    Z "Zeta existe desde hace siglos."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1948
translate spanish d6b150_1769dee4:

    # Z "But from what I've seen, the decayed know how to use old technology to advance their goals."
    Z "Pero por lo que he visto, los decaídos saben utilizar la vieja tecnología para avanzar en sus objetivos."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1949
translate spanish d6b150_a265373f:

    # Z "They are making strides in recovering the old ways of life."
    Z "Están avanzando en la recuperación de las antiguas formas de vida."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1950
translate spanish d6b150_4f2425e8:

    # Z "This means they are rediscovering old technology and means of combat."
    Z "Esto significa que están redescubriendo la antigua tecnología y los medios de combate."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1951
translate spanish d6b150_3e5c6314:

    # Z "Sticking to swords and our rigid culture might not work, in the long run."
    Z "Atenerse a las espadas y a nuestra rígida cultura podría no funcionar, a la larga."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1952
translate spanish d6b150_95781254:

    # Z "It could very well be that Zeta will one day be conquered."
    Z "Es muy posible que Zeta sea conquistada algún día."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1956
translate spanish d6b150_6f1b0177:

    # S "Let us hope that will never happen."
    S "Esperemos que eso no ocurra nunca."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1957
translate spanish d6b150_37f970f7:

    # S "I can't think of any culture that offers more than what we have now."
    S "No puedo pensar en ninguna cultura que ofrezca más de lo que tenemos ahora."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1958
translate spanish d6b150_5b68d914:

    # S "I don't know how those mutants you talked about see society..."
    S "No sé cómo ven la sociedad esos mutantes de los que hablas..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1959
translate spanish d6b150_baf62959:

    # S "But a decayed-ruled Egypt... a nightmare."
    S "Pero un Egipto gobernado por los Decaídos... una pesadilla."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1962
translate spanish d6b150_0a52ca7f:

    # Z "All we can do is wait and see..."
    Z "Todo lo que podemos hacer es esperar y ver..."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1963
translate spanish d6b150_23759fbb:

    # Z "Bide our time and jump to it when opportunity presents itself and a clear path forwards is forged."
    Z "Esperar el momento y saltar a él cuando se presente la oportunidad y se forje un camino claro hacia adelante."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1966
translate spanish d6b150_5b546de8:

    # S "Even if that happens, we will find a way."
    S "Aunque eso ocurra, encontraremos una manera."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1967
translate spanish d6b150_dd4a3307:

    # S "Zeta is not the end all be all."
    S "Zeta no es el fin de todo."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1968
translate spanish d6b150_6ce45830:

    # S "I'm sure we could come up on top even if the city was overrun by raiders."
    S "Estoy segura de que podríamos salir adelante aunque la ciudad fuera invadida por los asaltantes."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1972
translate spanish d6b150_56f977fe:

    # S "And from what I heard, you already started climbing their ranks!"
    S "Y por lo que he oído, ¡ya has empezado a escalar en sus filas!"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1975
translate spanish d6b150_fa469abe:

    # Z "Ha, let us wait and see, young woman."
    Z "Ha, esperemos a ver, jovencita."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1981
translate spanish d6b151_6247293d:

    # S "So... want to tell me how this new ride of yours works?"
    S "Bueno que... ¿Me vas a contar cómo funciona este nuevo transporte tuyo?"

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1986
translate spanish d6b151_1f3aa5c3:

    # Z "You bet. But your [persistent.mom] should be done with the evening meal soon, so let's be quick."
    Z "Ya lo creo. Pero tu [persistent.mom] no tardará en terminar la cena, así que seamos rápidos."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1989
translate spanish d6b151_b9d8c295:

    # "{i}You show [S] the new car in detail."
    "{i}Le enseñas a [S] el coche nuevo con todo detalle."

# game/scripts/day6.rpy:1990
translate spanish d6b151_024861cc:

    # "{i}Later after dinner, you eventually head to sleep."
    "{i}Más tarde, después de la cena, os vais a dormir."

